<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Timing Gear Train and Front
        Cover - Install - Install Idler Gear Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010805.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Install Idler Gear Assembly</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para id="s210010805.2.1">When an engine has been disassembled and camshaft, crankshaft or idler gear
                    removed, gears must be assembled with timing marks properly aligned.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Single punch marks on crankshaft and lower idler gear and camshaft and upper idler gear must
                    align, while two punch marks on both idler gears must align.
                </para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Once assembled at "marks aligned" position, engine will require 34 crankshaft revolutions to
                    return to "marks aligned" position again.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f210010828" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Align timing marks</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Upper idler gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lower idler gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install lower idler gear with timing marks facing out.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align crankshaft gear and lower idler gear timing marks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten retaining bolt to "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_230.xml" xrefid="t210010802">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                ."
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify measurement of crankshaft gear and lower idler gear backlash to confirm proper
                assembly. See "Measure Gear Train Backlash Prior to Removal" in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010829" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5317.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install lower idler gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install upper idler gear with timing marks facing out.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align camshaft gear, upper idler gear and lower idler gear timing marks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new upper idler gear retaining bolt in upper idler gear. Tighten retaining bolt to "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_230.xml" xrefid="t210010802">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                ."
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify measurement of camshaft gear, lower idler gear, and upper idler gear backlash to
                confirm proper assembly. See "Measure Gear Train Backlash Prior to Removal" in this section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010830" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5315.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install upper idler gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install high-pressure pump in rear cover. Use new gasket. See "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_S210011204.xml" xrefid="s210011204.1.1">High-pressure Oil Pump</hotlnk>
                " in the "High-pressure Lube Oil System" section in this manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place new O-ring on oil pressure relief valve and install oil pressure relief valve in
                crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010831" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5305.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install oil pressure relief valve</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
